On Mon, Mar 29, 1999 at 12:26:24PM +0200, Andreas Schwab wrote:
> What's wrong with gdb?
It requires a sane stack frame -- something which wastes a register
when tuning asm up the wazoo.
Aside from that, it's a horrible debugger for assembly. Something
like Borland Turbo Debugger would be nice at times... (not the gui
necessarily, but that level of functionality).
